cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
authors:
  - name: "Ignacio Arancibia"
  - name: "Claude Sonnet 4.6 (Anthropic)"
title: "Thirty-Seven Years of Simulated Annealing on a Causal Set: A Revival of Bombelli (1987) with 2026 Tools"
version: 1.0.0
date-released: "2026-05-20"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/ignacioarancibia/bombelli"
abstract: >
  A faithful Python 3.12 port of Luca Bombelli's 1987 Pascal program for embedding
  causal sets into Minkowski spacetime by simulated annealing, together with an
  empirical characterisation of the algorithm using 2026 tools: GPU acceleration,
  ensemble statistics, order-theoretic invariants, and AI collaboration.
keywords:
  - causal set theory
  - simulated annealing
  - quantum gravity
  - discrete spacetime
  - computational archaeology
